Plot Load

Variance

data %>% 
  group_by(date, hour) %>% 
  summarise(total_load = sum(total_load)) %>% 
  mutate(month = month(date, label=T)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=hour, y = total_load, group = date, color=month))+
  geom_line(alpha=0.1)+
  facet_wrap('month')+
  theme_bw()+
  theme(legend.position='none')
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'date'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.

Relationship with Temperature

data %>% 
  filter(year>2020) %>% 
  group_by(date, hour, year ,holiday_flag) %>% 
  summarise(total_load = sum(total_load), 
            average_temp = mean(average_temp, na.rm=T)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=average_temp, y=total_load)) +
  geom_point(alpha=0.3)+
  facet_wrap('year')+
  theme_bw()+
  geom_smooth(method='loess')
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'date', 'hour', 'year'. You can override
## using the `.groups` argument.
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 5853 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_smooth()`).
## Warning: Removed 5853 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).
